{"image_id": "KEY_2013_page_67", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "Our federal tax (benefit) expense differs from the amount that would be calculated using the federal statutory tax", "bbox": [162.5, 159.1, 1104.6, 179.9]}, {"text": "rate, primarily because we generate income from investments in tax-advantaged assets, such as corporate-owned", "bbox": [162.5, 184.1, 1102.0, 204.9]}, {"text": "life insurance, earn credits associated with investments in low-income housing projects, and make periodic", "bbox": [162.5, 209.1, 1054.6, 229.9]}, {"text": "adjustments to our tax reserves. In addition, in 2013 and 2012, our effective tax rate was lower due to the early", "bbox": [162.5, 234.1, 1086.9, 254.9]}, {"text": "termination of certain leveraged leases that resulted in nontaxable gains pursuant to a prior settlement with the", "bbox": [162.5, 259.1, 1083.4, 279.9]}, {"text": "IRS.", "bbox": [162.5, 284.1, 200.1, 304.9]}, {"text": "We recorded a valuation allowance of $1 million and $3 million at December 31, 2013, and 2012, respectively,", "bbox": [162.5, 329.8, 1091.2, 350.6]}, {"text": "against the gross deferred tax assets for certain state net operating loss and state credit carryforwards.", "bbox": [162.5, 354.8, 1007.8, 375.6]}, {"text": "Line of Business Results", "bbox": [162.5, 397.1, 420.1, 422.1]}, {"text": "This section summarizes the financial performance and related strategic developments of our two major business", "bbox": [162.5, 446.3, 1105.2, 467.1]}, {"text": "segments (operating segments): Key Community Bank and Key Corporate Bank. Note 23 (“Line of Business", "bbox": [162.5, 471.3, 1072.5, 492.1]}, {"text": "Results”) describes the products and services offered by each of these business segments, provides more detailed", "bbox": [162.5, 496.3, 1104.9, 517.1]}, {"text": "financial information pertaining to the segments and certain lines of business, and explains “Other Segments”", "bbox": [162.5, 521.3, 1077.9, 542.1]}, {"text": "and “R